<subSubSection pageId="86" pageNumber="87" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="86.[151,1437,1013,1760]" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1301,1327]" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">Remarks</emphasis>
. This species is widely distributed in northern Eurasia. In 
<collectingCountry box="[985,1056,1302,1328]" name="South Korea" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">Korea</collectingCountry>
, it has been found only in Gosui [=Hapsu], Hakugan [=Paegam] and Tonai [=Tonae], all in 
<collectingRegion box="[808,975,1337,1363]" country="North Korea" name="Yanggang-do" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">Ryanggang-do</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[985,1126,1337,1364]" name="North Korea" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">North Korea</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Takeuchi, K." box="[1141,1311,1337,1363]" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" pagination="173 - 229" refId="ref80448" refString="Takeuchi, K. (1938) A systematic study on the suborder Symphyta (Hymenoptera) of the Japanese Empire (1). Tenthredo, 2, 173 - 229." type="journal article" year="1938">Takeuchi 1938</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A." pageId="86" pageNumber="87" pagination="346 - 359" refId="ref76075" refString="Shinohara, A. (1985 b) The sawfly genus Onycholyda (Hymenoptera, Pamphiliidae) of Japan I. Kontyu, Tokyo, 53, 346 - 359." type="journal article" year="1985">Shinohara 1985b</bibRefCitation>
) and the confirmed host plants of this species are 
<taxonomicName box="[784,893,1374,1400]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rosa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[784,840,1374,1399]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">Rosa</emphasis>
spp.
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Taeger, A. &amp; Altenhofer, E. &amp; Blank, S. M. &amp; Jansen, E. &amp; Kraus, M. &amp; Pschorn-Walcher, H. &amp; Ritzau, C." box="[908,1115,1373,1399]" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" pagination="49 - 135" refId="ref80046" refString="Taeger, A., Altenhofer, E., Blank, S. M., Jansen, E., Kraus, M., Pschorn-Walcher, H. &amp; Ritzau, C. (1998) Kommentare zur Biologie, Verbreitung und Gefahrdung der Pflanzenwespen Deutschlands (Hymenoptera, Symphyta). In: Taeger, A. &amp; Blank, S. M. (Eds), Pflanzenwespen Deutschlands (Hymenoptera, Symphyta). Kommentierte Bestandsaufnahme. Goecke &amp; Evers, Keltern, pp. 49 - 135." type="book chapter" year="1998">
Taeger 
<emphasis box="[992,1049,1373,1399]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">et al.</emphasis>
1998
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Vikberg, V." box="[1126,1283,1373,1399]" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" pagination="439 - 459" refId="ref80692" refString="Vikberg, V. (2002) Rearing experiments on Finnish species of Pamphiliidae (Hymenoptera), with special emphasis on the egg laying behaviour. In: Viitasaari, M. (Ed.), Sawflies (Hymenoptera, Symphyta) I. Tremex Press, Helsinki, pp. 439 - 459." type="book chapter" year="2002">Vikberg 2002</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A. &amp; Hara, H." pageId="86" pageNumber="87" pagination="159 - 161" refId="ref77774" refString="Shinohara, A. &amp; Hara, H. (2006) Pamphilius balteatus (Hymenoptera, Pamphiliidae), a leaf-rolling sawfly feeding on Rosa acicularis in Hokkaido. Japanese Journal of Systematic Entomology, 12, 159 - 161." type="journal article" year="2006">Shinohara &amp; Hara 2006</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Lee, J. - W. &amp; Choi, J. - K. &amp; Park, B." box="[291,476,1409,1436]" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" pagination="1 - 96" refId="ref74711" refString="Lee, J. - W., Choi, J. - K. &amp; Park, B. (2019) Synoptic list of Symphyta (Hymenoptera) in Korea. Journal of Species Research, 8, 1 - 96." type="journal article" year="2019">
Lee 
<emphasis box="[339,395,1409,1435]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">et al.</emphasis>
(2019)
</bibRefCitation>
included 
<collectingCountry box="[585,725,1409,1436]" name="South Korea" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">South Korea</collectingCountry>
in the distribution of this species and 
<bibRefCitation author="Sundukov, Yu. N." box="[1146,1341,1409,1435]" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" pagination="20 - 117" refId="ref79858" refString="Sundukov, Yu. N. (2017) Suborder Symphyta - Sawflies and wood wasps. In: Lelej, A. S., Proshchalykin, M. Yu. &amp; Loktionov, V. M. (Eds.), Annotated catalogue of the Hymenoptera of Russia. Vol. I. Symphyta and Apocrita: Aculeata. Proceedings of the Zoological Institute of the Russian Academy of Sciences, Supplement 6, pp. 20 - 117." type="journal article" year="2017">Sundukov (2017)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Lee, J. - W. &amp; Choi, J. - K. &amp; Park, B." pageId="86" pageNumber="87" pagination="1 - 96" refId="ref74711" refString="Lee, J. - W., Choi, J. - K. &amp; Park, B. (2019) Synoptic list of Symphyta (Hymenoptera) in Korea. Journal of Species Research, 8, 1 - 96." type="journal article" year="2019">
Lee 
<emphasis box="[151,208,1445,1471]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">et al.</emphasis>
(2019)
</bibRefCitation>
gave 
<taxonomicName box="[358,461,1446,1471]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Fragaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[358,461,1446,1471]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">Fragaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[475,556,1446,1471]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Prunus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[475,556,1446,1471]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">Prunus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[611,698,1446,1472]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Spiraea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[611,698,1446,1472]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">Spiraea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as additional hosts without presenting new data or relevant references. These distribution and host records need confirmation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="86.[151,1437,1013,1760]" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">
In the key by 
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A. &amp; Lelej, A. S." box="[364,663,1517,1543]" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" pagination="922 - 942" refId="ref78590" refString="Shinohara, A. &amp; Lelej, A. S. (2007) 2. Sem. Pamphiliidae - Pautinnye Pilil'shchiki, ili Pilil'shchiki-tkachi. In: Lelej, A. S. (Ed.), Setchatokryloobraznye, Skorpionnitsy, Pereponchatokrylye. Ch. 5. Opredelitel' Nasekomykh Dal'nego Vostoka Rossii. Tom IV. Dal'nauka, Vladivostok, pp. 922 - 942." type="book chapter" year="2007">Shinohara &amp; Lelej (2007)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Konow" authorityYear="1897" box="[677,810,1517,1543]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="balteatus">
<emphasis box="[677,810,1517,1543]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">P. balteatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
will erroneously run to 
<taxonomicName box="[1093,1160,1518,1543]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="itoi">
<emphasis box="[1093,1160,1518,1543]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">P. itoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, because 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Konow" authorityYear="1897" box="[1275,1408,1517,1543]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="balteatus">
<emphasis box="[1275,1408,1517,1543]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">P. balteatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is wrongly placed under couplet 19, whereas it should be placed under couplet 16 (then 18). This error has been corrected in the new key given above.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="86.[151,1437,1013,1760]" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">
In our COI analysis (
<figureCitation box="[445,545,1625,1651]" captionStart="FIGURE 148" captionStartId="235.[151,250,1827,1851]" captionTargetBox="[157,1427,198,1794]" captionTargetId="figure-19@235.[151,1436,181,1803]" captionTargetPageId="235" captionText="FIGURE 148. Condensed ML tree based on CO1 gene sequences, with details of Pamphilius vafer group, part 1." pageId="86" pageNumber="87">Fig. 148</figureCitation>
), 
<specimenCount box="[567,727,1625,1651]" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" type="generic">six specimens</specimenCount>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[800,905,1625,1651]" name="Germany" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">Germany</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[919,1005,1625,1651]" name="Finland" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">Finland</collectingCountry>
and Primorskij Kraj formed a monophyletic group with 97% UFBoot support. The clade of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Konow" authorityYear="1897" box="[769,898,1661,1687]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="balteatus">
<emphasis box="[769,898,1661,1687]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">P. balteatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[1096,1201,1661,1687]" name="Germany" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">Germany</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1212,1298,1661,1687]" name="Finland" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">Finland</collectingCountry>
and Primorskij Kraj) was retrieved as the sister group of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kontuniemi" authorityYear="1946" box="[693,828,1697,1723]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Prunus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="thorwaldi">
<emphasis box="[693,828,1697,1723]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">P. thorwaldi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
subgroup (
<taxonomicName authority="Maa, 1950" authorityName="Maa" authorityYear="1950" box="[953,1187,1697,1724]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lobatus">
<emphasis box="[953,1062,1697,1723]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="87">P. lobatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Maa, T." box="[1068,1187,1697,1724]" pageId="86" pageNumber="87" pagination="14 - 21" refId="ref74871" refString="Maa, T. (1950) New or little known Chinese sawflies and woodwasps (Hymenoptera). Quarterly Journal of Taiwan Museum, Taipei, 3, 14 - 21." type="journal article" year="1950">Maa, 1950</bibRefCitation>
